<section id="contest">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="description span8">
				<ul class="large">
					<li>Pick an Indian Government website of your choice.</li>
					<li>Redesign the homepage by introducing the concepts of design, aesthetics, information architecture and usability.</li>
					<li>Awe the world.</li>
				</ul>

				<p class="legible">If it is hard for you to think of them, here are a few who have expressed their interest in taking a look at how they could be better:</p>
				
				<ul class="legible">
					<li><a href="http://mcgm.gov.in/">Municipal Corporation of Greater Mumbai</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://www.bescom.org/">Bangalore Electric Supply Company</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://delhigovt.nic.in/bhagidari.asp">Bhagidari of Delhi Govt.</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://www.bestundertaking.com/">B.E.S.T.</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://censusindia.gov.in/">Census of India</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://www.doccentre.net/">Centre for Education and Documentation</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			
			<div class="legible span4">
				<p>It’s 2012 and the web today is undisputedly the worlds biggest platform. Over the past two decades most things about the web has changed — be it the utility, the technologies, or even the interfaces.</p>

				<p>Sadly most Indian Government institutions are still sleeping in the past, their websites appear to be totally aloof about these changes— directionless, heartless and a pain for the users. All of us have have cribbed about it at least once in our past. Many around us express their annoyance about this everyday.</p>

				<p>We think it&#8217;s high time to be the change. It&#8217;s time to show the community, the Government and the people at large how you think these websites should be shaped going forward.</p>
			</div>
		</div><!-- /row -->
		<hr class="divider">
	</div><!-- /container -->
</section><!-- /contest -->



<section id="rules" class="section">
	<div class="container">
		<h2>Rules</h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="description legible span8">
				<ul>
					<li>We ♥ HTML, CSS and JavaScript. Please submit solutions that render best on a browser, not in Photoshop, not in Fireworks, not in Flash, not as an image.</li>
					<li>Compatibility with the latest versions of Chrome and Firefox should do.</li>
					<li>Feel free to use any CSS/JavaScript frameworks/libraries that make your work easier.</li>
					<li>Do <em>not</em> use any resources that you do not have rights for. This applies as much to photos and graphics as it does to code.</li>
					<li>Entries should be purely front-end and not have any dependency on the server or server-side technologies.</li>
				</ul>
			</div><!-- span8 -->
			<div class="span4">
				<div class="notice legible">
					<p>Write to us with any questions or doubts you may have about this.</p>
					<p class="large"><a href="mailto:metarefresh@hasgeek.in">metarefresh@hasgeek.in</a></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div><!-- /row -->
		<hr class="divider">
	</div><!-- /container -->
</section><!-- /rules -->


